No, 55/4/CF-62
GO VE RNMENT OF INDIA
CABINET SECRETARIAT
(Department of Cabinet Affairs)
IMMEDIATE
New Delhi, the 8th June 1962,
The undersigned is directed to state that Shri T.T.
Krishnamachari, Cabinet Minister without portfolio, and
Shri Prakash Chandra Se thi, Deputy Minister in the Ministry
of Steel & Heavy Industries, assumed office with effect from
the forenoon of Friday, June 8, 1962,
( B.G. Rau )
Joint Secretary to the Cabinet.
To
All Members of the Council of Ministers,
Copy forwarded to the Principal Private Secretary to the
Prime Minister/the PriÍvate Secretary to the Prime Minister,
for information,
Copy forwarded to the Secretary to the President/the
Private Secretary to the Vice-President, for information.
Helan
( B.G. Rau)
Joint Secretary to the Cabinet,
Copy forwarded to all Secretaries/Special Secretaries/
Additional Secretaries to the Government of India/the Chairman,
Railway Board, for information,
Copy forwarded to all Ministries of the Government of
India/Department of Parliamentary Affairs/Planning Commission/
Department of Atomic Energy/Prime Mini ster's Secretariat/
Lok Sabha Secretariat/Rajya Sabha Secretariat, for information.
( D.P. Chopra )
Under Secretary to the Cabinet.
"KSC"
350 copies.
